        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Starrsville to Calvin to near McElheneys Crossroads,
and moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Mansfield, Madison, Harmony, Godfrey, Monticello, Warfield, Shady
Dale, Willard, Rock Eagle 4-H Center, Buckhead, Central Georgia
Experiment Stn, Eatonton, Newborn, Calvin, Farrar, Rutledge, Swords,
Stanfordville, Adgateville, and Apalachee.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for central and
north central Georgia.</instruction>
